\begin_inset Formula $\left(c_{i}\right)_{i\in I\subseteq\mathbb{N}}$
\end_inset

 (depending on 
\begin_inset Formula $\KET{\psi}$
\end_inset

) with:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\KET{\psi} & =\sum_{i\in I}c_{i}\KET{\phi_{i}}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

If 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\langle \phi_{i},\phi_{j}\right\rangle =\delta_{ij}$
\end_inset

, then the basis is 
\emph on
complete
\emph default
 and 
\emph on
orthonormal
\emph default
.
