\emph on
Representation
\emph default
: Assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\KET{\phi_{i}}\right)_{i\in I\subseteq\mathbb{N}}$
\end_inset

 (respectively 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\KET q\right)_{q\in\mathbb{R}}$
\end_inset

) is a complete orthonormal basis.
 The ket 
\begin_inset Formula $\KET{\psi}$
\end_inset

 is said to “be represented” in that basis by associating:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
 & \text{discrete case} &  & \text{continous case}\\
\BRA{\psi} & \mapsto\left(\begin{array}{c}
\BraKet{\phi_{1}|\psi}\\
\BraKet{\phi_{2}|\psi}\\
\vdots
\end{array}\right)\in\mathbb{C}^{\left|I\right|} & \KET{\psi} & \mapsto\BraKet{q|\psi}=:\psi\left(q\right)\\
\BRA{\psi} & \mapsto\left(\begin{array}{c}
\BraKet{\phi_{1}|\psi}^{*}\\
\BraKet{\phi_{2}|\psi}^{*}\\
\vdots
\end{array}\right)\in\mathbb{C}^{\left|I\right|} & \BRA{\psi} & \mapsto\BraKet{q|\psi}^{*}=\psi\left(q\right)^{*}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

This 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi\left(q\right)$
\end_inset

